   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON FIFTEEN TAKING HEED HOW TO BUILD Scripture Reading: 1 Cor 3:10-15 OUTLINE The unique foundation having been laid vv.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>10a, 11.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Building on the unique foundation v. 10m.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Building with gold, silver, and precious stones v. 12a: Gold symbolizing God's nature.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Silver symbolizing Christ's redemptive work.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Precious stones symbolizing the Spirit's transforming work.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Building with wood, grass, and stubble v. 12b: Wood signifying human nature.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Grass signifying man in the flesh Isa 40:6-7.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Stubble signifying lifelessness.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Every man's work will be tested by fire vv.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>13-15: If any man's work stands the fire, he will receive a reward.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>If any man's work is consumed, he will suffer loss: He himself will be saved.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Yet so as through fire.</S>
   </TEXT>
